This is the default.
.TP
.B \-stepmap \fIs0\
\fR[\fB,\fIs1\
\fR[\fB,\fIs2\
\fR[\fB,\fIs3\
\fR[\fB,\fIs4\
\fR[\fB,\fIs5\
\fR[\fB,\fIs6\
\fR[\fB,\fIs7\
\fR]]]]]]]
(Linux only)
Selectively set double-step mode for individual real floppy drives.
Each comma-delimited parameter corresponds to a drive unit number; see
.BR "Real floppy disks" ,
above.
If
.IR s U
is
.B 1
and
.IR disk M \- U
is a (symbolic link to) a real drive,
where
.I M
is the TRS-80 model
.RB ( 1 ,
.BR 3 ,
.BR 4 ,
or
.BR 4p )
